-- South Africa Leaves Its Corn Crop Forecast Unchanged at 13.3 Million Tons
-- Carli Lourens
-- 2010-06-24T12:31:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/south-africa-leaves-its-corn-crop-forecast-unchanged-at-13-3-million-tons.html

          
          
             South Africa left its corn crop
forecast for this season unchanged at 13.3 million metric tons
and raised its sunflower seed crop estimate 3.9 percent to
528,765 tons, Department of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries
official Marda Scheepers said in a telephone interview from
Pretoria today.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        